  "ciliary_role": "Has an important role in regulating microtubule length in cilia by facilitating tubulin addition to ciliary  and might also be involved in regulating other factors, possibly by interacting with Nek1. Cep104 is involved in the stabilization of the ciliary axoneme or in cilia formation and elongation, mutations cause ciliopathies (28017521). Regulates ciliary assembly by interacting with centriolar proteins that suppress cilia formation, detaches from these proteins at the onset of cilia formation and moves to the tip of the  scent cilium (23970417).",
